     April 15 (Bloomberg) --Nico Rosbergof Mercedes won the
Chinese Grand Prix to claim his first Formula One race victory.  Rosberg, who started in pole position, finished 20.6
seconds ahead of McLarenâ€™s Jenson Button in the 56-lap event at
Shanghai International Circuit.  Lewis Hamilton  of McLaren was
third ahead of Red Bull duo Mark Webber and Sebastian Vettel.  Michael Schumacher , who started second on the grid
alongside teammate Rosberg, quit the race shortly after his
first pit stop.  The Bahrain Grand Prix, the fourth event in the 20-race
2012 world championship, is scheduled April 22.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
